    "title": "Future Shock! The Story of 2000AD",
    "updated": "2015-06-18 17:50:04",
    "description": "<p>Future Shock! is a long overdue document of the magazine that kick-started the careers of Alan Moore (<em>Watchmen<\/em>) and Grant Morrison (<em>All-Star Superman<\/em>), created Judge Dredd and inspired Hollywood (<em>RoboCop<\/em>, <em>Alien<\/em>). Featuring interviews with 2000 AD creator Pat Mills, writers Neil Gaiman and Dave Gibbons and Dredd screenwriter Alex Garland, this fascinating documentary can only be described as: Zarjaz!<\/p>\n<p>See the film as a double bill with <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http:\/\/www.edfilmfest.org.uk\/films\/2015\/dredd-3d\"><em>Dredd<\/em><\/a> in awesome 3D!<\/p>\n<h2>Doc of the Day<\/h2>\n<p>This Scottish Premiere is our <a href=\"http:\/\/www.edfilmfest.org.uk\/films\/doc-of-the-day\">Doc of the Day<\/a> and following the screening, enjoy a Q&amp;A session, hosted by celebrated film critic Kim Newman with:<\/p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Director Paul Goodwin<\/li>\n    <li>Judge Dredd writer Emma Beeby<\/li>\n    <li>2000AD creator Pat Mills<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>We are also hosting an extra special <em>Bite Me Fanboy<\/em> event at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.edfilmfest.org.uk\/films\/festival-hq\">Festival HQ<\/a>.<\/p>",
